com.amazonaws.greengrass.streammanager.client.config

Class StreamManagerAuthInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazonaws.greengrass.streammanager.client.config.StreamManagerAuthInfo

  • public class StreamManagerAuthInfo
extends Object
    Auth info to be sent to the StreamManager server for Auth. Currently this is done by passing authToken to the server. When the StreamManager client is running inside a Greengrass lambda, the value of the authToken is populated automatically from the environment variable set by Greengrass core (STREAM_MANAGER_AUTH_TOKEN_KEY) This tells ServerManager that the calling process is part of the Greengrass group and thus has permissions to access StreamManager resources.

    When the StreamManager server is started with the environment variable "streammanager.auth.authenticate_client" set to False, StreamManager server will ignore this config. This is achieved by configuring the StreamManager function definition
